EXERCISE 3  
When we speak English, Very often two words are joined together as contracted forms.  
The following are some examples:  
Can + not = cannot = can’t  
Do + not = do not = Don’t  
Ans: -  
Can + not = cannot = can’t  
Will + not = will not = won’t  
Does + not = does not = doesn’t  
Have + not = have not = haven’t  
It + will = it will = it’ll  
It + is = it is = it’s  
Did + not = did not = didn’t  
You + will = you will = you’ll

EXERCISE 5  
COMPREHENSION  
1
. Why was Keith Koppel glad to leave the patient’s room?  
Ans: - Keith Koppel was glad to leave the patient’s room because he had a tiring morning  
trying to get Ellsworth to cooperate in his own recovery.  
2
. What works of Collis P. Ellsworth caused concern to his doctor?  
Ans: - The doctor was concerned about his obsession with business. He had recently begun to  
make big mistakes. He insisted on buying companies at very high prices only to watch them  
fail or go bankrupt.  
Page | 3  
3
. What did Dr. Caswell prescribe for his patient to avoid further health problem?  
Ans: - Dr. Caswell suggested him to take up art to divert his mind from business and to  
avoid further health problems.  
4
. What was the unexpected request of Ellsworth’s to Frank Swain?  
Ans: - The unexpected request of Ellsworth to Frank Swain was to visit him more  
frequently.  
5
. How often did Ellsworth want Swain to come?  
Ans: - Ellsworth wanted Swain to come twice a week or perhaps three times a week.  
6
. What was the difference between the first and second drawings of Ellsworth?  
Ans: - At first Ellsworth drew several lines and connected them crudely. But in the next  
week his drawings had a slight resemblance to a vase. There was improvement in his  
drawing  
7
. Who was Judson Livingstone?  
Ans: - Judson Livingstone was the head of the Atlantic Art Institute and a friend of Dr  
Caswell.  
8
. Why did the doctor think that it was safe to allow Ellsworth to visit the  
Metropolitan Museum?  
Ans: - The doctor thought that it was safe to allow Ellsworth to visit the Metropolitan  
Museum because his treatment was working perfectly.  
9
. Why was the summer show at the Lathrop Gallery the biggest art exhibition?  
Ans: - The summer show at the Lathrop Gallery was the biggest art exhibition because it  
was the lifetime dream of every important artist in the United States to get a prize from  
this exhibition.  
1
0. Did the doctor succeed in his art of treatment of Ellsworth?  
Ans: - No, the doctor did not succeed in the treatment of Ellsworth because even after the  
treatment business was uppermost in his mind.

EXERCISE 6  
COMPOSITION  
1
. What were the causes of the ailment of Mr. Ellsworth?  
Ans: - Mr. Ellsworth was a very rich business man and his failure in business was the  
main causes of his ailment. He had suffered his last heart attack after his disastrous  
purchase of a small rail road in Iowa. He suffered health problems over the failure of a  
chain of grocery stores, and all his recent purchases had to be closed down.  
2
. Why did the doctor think of teaching art to his patient?  
Ans: - The doctor realized that the old man needed something which would take his mind  
off from his problems and redirect his energies. So, he thought of teaching art to his  
patient to divert his mind from business.  
3
. Why did the Lathrop Gallery accept the painting of Mr. Collis Ellsworth?  
Ans: - The Lathrop Gallery accepted the painting of Mr. Collis Ellsworth because he was  
the owner of the gallery. He had bought the Gallery last month.  
4
. Why was Dr. Caswell Worried when Mr. Ellsworth insisted on showing his  
painting?  
Ans: - Dr Caswell was worried because His painting was simply horrible. Further he  
announced that he was going to exhibit his painting in the summer show at the Lathrop  
Gallery. And he thought that if they saw his picture everyone will laugh at him.  
5
. How did Collis P. Ellsworth befool the doctor and his art tutor?  
Ans: - Dr Caswell thought that his plan to teach Mr. Ellsworth art to divert his mind and  
energies from his business problems was successful. But they could not change his mind  
and they found out that business was still uppermost in his mind. And he ended up buying  
the art gallery instead.
